TITLE: Creating Colorful Circles with React Native Skia
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to use React Native Skia to draw three overlapping circles with cyan, magenta, and yellow colors using the multiply blend mode. The code creates a canvas with specified dimensions and renders a group of circles with defined positions and radii.

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import React from "react";
import { Canvas, Circle, Group } from "@shopify/react-native-skia";

const App = () => {
  const width = 256;
  const height = 256;
  const r = width * 0.33;
  return (
    <Canvas style={{ width, height }}>
      <Group blendMode="multiply">
        <Circle cx={r} cy={r} r={r} color="cyan" />
        <Circle cx={width - r} cy={r} r={r} color="magenta" />
        <Circle cx={width / 2} cy={width - r} r={r} color="yellow" />
      </Group>
    </Canvas>
  );
};

export default App;
```

