TITLE: Simple Shader Component Implementation in React Native Skia
DESCRIPTION: This example shows how to create a SimpleShader component that renders a gradient by mapping x and y coordinates to color channels. The shader is applied to a Fill component inside a Canvas.

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import {Skia, Canvas, Shader, Fill} from "@shopify/react-native-skia";

const source = Skia.RuntimeEffect.Make(`
vec4 main(vec2 pos) {
  // normalized x,y values go from 0 to 1, the canvas is 256x256
  vec2 normalized = pos/vec2(256);
  return vec4(normalized.x, normalized.y, 0.5, 1);
}`)!;

const SimpleShader = () => {
  return (
    <Canvas style={{ width: 256, height: 256 }}>
      <Fill>
        <Shader source={source} />
      </Fill>
    </Canvas>
  );
};
```

