TITLE: Loading and Displaying SVG Images in React Native Skia
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to load an SVG file using useSVG hook and display it in a Canvas using the ImageSVG component. The code handles conditional rendering when the SVG is loaded.

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import {
  Canvas,
  ImageSVG,
  useSVG
} from "@shopify/react-native-skia";

const ImageSVGDemo = () => {
  // Alternatively, you can pass an SVG URL directly
  // for instance: const svg = useSVG("https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fd/Ghostscript_Tiger.svg");
  const svg = useSVG(require("../../assets/tiger.svg"));
  return (
    <Canvas style={{ flex: 1 }}>
      { svg && (
        <ImageSVG
          svg={svg}
          width={256}
          height={256}
        />)
      }
    </Canvas>
  );
};
```

